        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-01-07T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-01-07T01:00:00-05:00" n="6" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d6">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">846G.00/1–748: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-01-07T14:00:00+08:00">January 7, 1948—2 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 8—4:26 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. Embassy noticed Hong Kong dateline Story appearing in Shanghai English
                    language press January 2 of formation of “Kmt Revolutionary Committee” in Hong
                    Kong under leadership of Li Chih-Sun<note n="15" xml:id="d6fn15">General Li
                        Chi-shen was expelled from the Kuomintang in 1947 because of anti-Government
                        activities.</note> and with cooperation of various other prominent dissident
                    Kmt members.</p>
                <p>Embassy would appreciate investigation and report on this development.<note n="16" xml:id="d6fn16">The Consul General at Hong Kong replied to the
                        Ambassador in letter of January 17, not glinted; see unnumbered despatch of
                        March 1 from the Consul General at Hong Kong, <ref target="#pg_126">p.
                            126</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent Hong Kong 3; repeated Dept.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
